  "texts": [
    "Overall, GPT-4 was more successful at coming up with divergent responses given the same number of opportunities to generate answers compared to the human counterpart and showed higher originality but only for specific prompts (Fig. 1).",
    "Next, we compared elaboration scores between humans and GPT-4.",
    "Fluency scores differ from elaboration in the sense that fluency accounts for each coherent response whereas elaboration quantifies the number of words per valid response.",
    "For example, a person could respond \"you could use a fork to knit or as a hair comb. \"",
    "In this example, the fluency would be 2 (knitting instrument and comb), but the elaboration would be 12 (number of words used in the response)."
  ],
